result.execSummary:
The defendant Victor Rentria was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate with Restricted Controlled Substance (2nd w/ Minor Pass. < 16 yrs.), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(am).
  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Possession of THC [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Victor Rentria in court with attorney Jeffery Joy.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 3:50 PM. Called 16CF100 and 16CM23. State - have complied with victim notificatio requirements with no response - resolved - submits exhibit #1 for 16CM23 case - Court receives exhibit #1 after no objections - 16CF100 - defendant would plead g/nc to counts #1 and #2, amend count #6 to county ordinance of bail jumping with $300 fine plus costs, on counts #7 and #8 - plead g/nc , cor counts #1 and #2 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years, concurrent to each other, with conditions of: $300 fine plus costs one each count, #1 - 90 days conditional jail, AODA and follow thru, anger management and psychological assessment with follow thru, maintain absolute sobriety, no entry, employment/school, 200 hours of community service, no possession of firearms during the term of probation; on counts #7 and #8 - $1000 fine plus costs on each, DRI counts #3, #4 and #5 - DRI; on 16CM23 - acknowledge one prior OWI convicition, plead g/nc to count #1 as alleged, 90 days jail - consecuutive to jail time on 16CF100, fine of $2293 fine, DL revocation for 24 months, IID to be determined by the Court, #2 - 30 days jail - concurrent to count #1 plus costs, #3 - plead to as alleged with $500 fine plus costs, dismiss and read in counts #3, #4 and #5. Joy and Rentria agree, forgot to include misd BJ counts. Court - 16CM23 - #4 and #5 - DRI, 16CF100 - DRI counts #3, #4 and #5, amends count 6 to county ordinance of BJ, pleads NC, finds G, fine of $300 plus costs - take bond posted. Rentria pleads NC to counts #1, #2, #7 and #8 as alleged. Rentria pleads NC to counts #1, #2 and #3 as alleged on 16CM23. Rentria does acknowledge three prior OWI convictions. Court has plea quesionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by waiving his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - submits exhibit #2 - also need a condition on 16CM23 of $35.00 to Forest County for blood draw -  follow joint recommendation. Joy makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - asks for 60 days jail instead of 90 days jail on 16CF100 and 45 days jail on 16CM23 - asks for credit for 10 days on 16CF100 and 2 days credit on 16CM23. Court does not believe any credit is due on 16CM23 and believes 8 days credit on 16CF100. Rentria makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 16CF100 - count #7 - $1000.00 fine plus costs - take bond posted, count #8 - $1000.00 fine plus costs - take bond posted or 60 DTP/CO; counts #1 and #2 - withhold sentence and place on probaton for 2 year, concurrent to each other but consecutive to jail term on 16CM23, with conditions of: count #1 - impose 5 months in FC jail - stayed if he has employment within 30 days of release from custody and if not employed - must start serving 5 months, $300.00 fine plus costs and surcharges - paid thru probation if no bond money is left, AODA and follow thru, anger management and psychological assessment with follow thru, obtain GED, attend at least one AA/NA or similar program per week, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, reimbuse Forest County $35.00 for blood draw - 30 DTP/CO, $300.00 fine plus costs - paid thru probation,  200 hours of community service, no possession of firearms during the term of probation; count #2 - $300 fine plus costs and surcharges - paid thru probation - same conditions except no additional jail time or community service; 16CM23 - count #1 - 90 days in FC jail - consecutive to jail time on 16CF100 - huber and good time allowed - credit for 8 days - stayed for 60 days to complete treatment program but no more than 60 days, report 24 months after completion of the program or by 8:30 AM the next day if not completed, fine of $2293 - 60 DTP/CO, AODA, 24 month DL revocation, IID on DL and any vehicles titled in his name for 24 months, commencing upon issuance of valid DL; count #2 - $500.00 plus costs - 60 DTP/CO; #3 - fine of $500.00 plus costs - 60 DTP/CO, submit DNA sample with expunction rights, right to appeal, adjourned. Court receives exhibits #1 & #2 and documents from Joy to be filed confidential.
